<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Manhattan College</h2>
<strong>Riverdale, NY</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students who have successfully taken one or more Advanced Placement Exams of the College Board may ask for advanced placement and/or credit. Dean of school to which application is made will decide on credit to be granted and college course or courses that may be omitted in place of AP Exams. Scores of 3, 4 or 5 required. Decision to grant advanced placement and/or credit based on such factors as equivalence to content of courses in college curricula and applicability of area of advanced study to prescribed or elective requirements of program in which student enrolled. Advanced placement and/or credit action taken only if student specifically requests consideration and submits official score reports. No grades assigned to courses credited.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://catalog.manhattan.edu/undergraduate/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

